      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BONDI PROPHET (3) turned in a nice effort last time out at the second run of the campaign and finished just over a length away from the winner in second over 1208m at Port Macquarie after being in the firing line on the bend. Peaking now and is nicely placed to take this out. ACE'S IN BLOOM (1) resumed over 1400m at Eagle Farm last start when she sat close to the speed before fading in the straight to finish ninth. This looks a fair bit easier and she gets a key booking in Looker. Gets her chance to break a long run of outs. ROARING SUCCESS (7) doesn't win out of turn but is a genuine enough type with two minor placings from three starts this prep. Was solid at his most recent run when third over 1460m at Esk. Not a great deal tougher this time and he should be near his top. Deserves plenty of thought. JIDAYUBORI (9) has been in the market at her last couple of starts but hasn't made an impression, last start running eighth at Dalby. Should be further improved and rates among the chanc",
